00:28:13.560 --> 00:28:14.590
JOSH BERNSTEIN: You
go to what?

00:28:14.590 --> 00:28:15.130
AUDIENCE: Pony Bar.

00:28:15.130 --> 00:28:15.790
JOSH BERNSTEIN: Oh, Pony Bar
is open open up there, too.

00:28:15.790 --> 00:28:18.670
Yeah, Pony Bar is
great, as well.

00:28:18.670 --> 00:28:20.360
And that's the thing, the fact
that we can have a discussion

00:28:20.360 --> 00:28:23.730
about what a great beer bars
there are in New York City.

00:28:23.730 --> 00:28:27.770
It used to be 10 years ago, it
was The Gate, Blind Tiger,

00:28:27.770 --> 00:28:29.150
Ginger Man and a few
other places.

00:28:29.150 --> 00:28:32.000
But it's just that things have
been going gangbusters in such

00:28:32.000 --> 00:28:33.260
a great way.

00:28:33.260 --> 00:28:35.540
I always liked, too,
New York City--

00:28:35.540 --> 00:28:37.480
sometimes, they get behind
in certain fields.

00:28:37.480 --> 00:28:39.860
But New York City always plays
catch up in a big way.

00:28:39.860 --> 00:28:41.760
